  "pages": [
    {
      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "Pres. Samuel Gompers and the\nAmerican Federation of Labor\nscored first blood in the suit filed\nin the United States courts by the\nBuck Stove & Range Co. of st.\nLouis. The company asked for an\ninjunction restraining the A. F. of\nl.. and affiliated unions from boy\ncotting it's products. The appica-\nton was denied in the lower court.\n\n\nThe suit is important in that it\ndefines the legal right of labor or\nCARNATIONS to enforce demands by\nplacing the goods of any firm on\nthe unfair list. The Buck company\nhas appealed to the United States\nsupreme court."
    }
